text: Fynes may refer to: *Fynes Moryson (or Morison) (1566–1630), travelled in the 1590s on the European continent and the eastern Mediterranean lands *Henry Fynes Clinton (1781–1852), English classical scholar and chronologist, born in Gamston, Nottinghamshire *Savatheda Fynes (born 1974), track and field sprint athlete, competing internationally for Bahamas ==See also== *Fiennes *Fyne (disambiguation)
title: Fynes
